## What I Learned

. I started 9 Linux Commands
. They are : 
1. pwd - print Working Directory
2. cd - Change Directory
3. ls - list files and Directory
4. mkdir - make directory
5. touch -for create file
6. cp - copy files / Directories
7. mv - move files / Directories
8. rm - remove files contents
9. cat - concatenate , display file contents

-> Which Command I found most Useful
ls & cat

